DURBAN &#8211; A man was shot dead on Currie Road, Berea after an alleged attempted hijacking on Sunday night.Kwazulu Natal Police have since launched a manhunt for the gang of men responsible for the man&#8217;s death. A woman who was in the man&#8217;s company allege that she left the man in his car going to remove clothes from the line.On return from she was stopped by one man and at gunpoint he robbed her of her cellphone.The woman was unharmed.Another two armed men in the mean time approached the man in the car and allegedly shot him. The man was seated in his red BMW when he was shot through the closed door.The man died at the scene.Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said police were investigating a case of murder.